# Named Exports Only

Suzume-client must not use `export default`. Every value, type, and component is exported by name. This keeps imports stable across renames, avoids "rename on import" drift, and lets editors flag unused exports reliably.

## Rules

- No `export default` anywhere in `suzume-client/**`.
- No anonymous default-exported components/functions.
- Barrel `index.ts` files re-export by name: `export { Foo } from "./Foo"`.
- Importers always use the braced form: `import { Foo } from "..."`.

## Allowed

- `import styles from "./X.module.css"` — CSS Modules expose the styles record as the module's default; this is a virtual module from the bundler, not source code, so it's exempt.

## Examples

```tsx
// BAD
export default function PracticeModePicker(props: Props) { ... }
import PracticeModePicker from "../components/practice-mode-picker";

// GOOD
export function PracticeModePicker(props: Props) { ... }
import { PracticeModePicker } from "../components/practice-mode-picker";
```

```ts
// BAD — barrel
export { default } from "./PracticeModePicker";

// GOOD — barrel
export { PracticeModePicker } from "./PracticeModePicker";
```

## Refactor checklist

- Replace `export default function Name(...)` with `export function Name(...)`.
- Replace trailing `export default Name;` with a named export at the declaration site.
- Update all importers from `import Name from "..."` to `import { Name } from "..."`.
- Update barrel files to re-export by name.
